Learning Outcomes: By the end of the course, a successful student should be able to:
1) understand the fundamental theory of transmission genetics and the relationship between genes and traits;
2) describe pedigree analysis and the inheritance of human genetic disorders;
3) apply scientific method and analyses with the underlying genetic principles
