courses.learning_outcomes:
1. A firm grasp of the characteristics of vascular plants (ferns, fern allies, gymnosperms and angiosperms) through examination of the whole organisms and slide sections of representative species;
2. Integration of such characteristics through problem-solving approaches to real situations.
3. Able to understand the diversity and evolutionary relationships of vertebrate animals and to identify vertebrates to major class phyla;
4. Understand the general body plan of vertebrate animals;
5. Able to perform dissection of major vertebrate animals and identify major organ systems;
6. Able to relate function to structure of vertebrate animals;
7. Able to demonstrate a clear understanding of major aspects of vertebrate anatomy through drawing biological diagrams;
8. Able to observe, recognize, draw annotated diagrams and label fine vertebrate animal structures using the microscope.
