Knowledge outcomes:
1. Acquire ability to comprehend the implication of how humans evolve and why is so different from other organisms;
2. Acquire core knowledge on how humans varies;
3. Acquire an educated understanding on how humans adapts to different environments and hence lead to variations between different populations.
Skills outcomes:
1. Acquire skills in literature survey using various sources including effective usage of information technologies and web-based searches;
2. Acquire good analytical and oral communication skills via class project presentation;
3. Acquire good problem solving skill via course assessment.
Values and attribute outcomes:
1. Acquire a positive attitude toward humans as one of the member of all living organisms but is unique;
2. Acquire an educated mind and responsible attitude and appreciation of humans is part of the nature.
知识成果：
掌握对人类如何演化及为何与其它生命这样的不同上的意义;
获取有关人类不同种族的差异的核心知识;
明白人类如何适应不同的环境和由此而引致人种上的差异。
技能成果：
掌握文献调查技能，包括使用信息技术和有效利从互联网中搜索中得到的各种来源;
通过班上研习课题获得良好的分析和沟通技巧;
通过课程评估建立良好的解决问题的技巧。
价值观和属性的成果：
对人类作为所有生物的其中而又独特的一员建立积极的态度
通过思想教育对人类是自然界的一部份建立正确的态度。.

Students would be able to
1. recall the basic knowledge and techniques about microbiology;
2. recognize the nature and impacts of microorganisms;
3. compare and contrast the characteristics of microorganisms to multicellular organisms;
4. relate the structural or physiological adaptations of microorganisms to their success in occupying niches;
5. apply some basic principles and knowledge of microbiology to real life situations;
6. explain how the strategies employed by pathogens can avoid the host defenses.
學生應該能夠
1. 知悉有關微生物學的基本知識和技術；
2. 認識微生物的性質和影響；
3. 比較和對比微生物和多細胞生物的特點；
4. 掌握微生物的結構或生理適應如何使他們能夠成功佔據其生態位；
5. 把一些微生物學上的基本原則和知識應用到現實生活的情境中；
6. 解釋病原體如何使用各種戰略來迴避宿主的防禦。

The students will know:
1. the diversity of fungi and non-vascular plants (algae and bryophytes);
2. the adaptive features of these organisms to their habitats;
3. the survival features of these organisms to propagate the species;
4. the significance of some of these organisms in causing damages to habitats, human health and properties;
5. the benefits of some of these organisms in improving health, supplying food and providing fuel as well as other resources.
學生會認識：
